1.name: Account
1.desc: Account mnemonic as agreed between buy and sell sides, e.g. broker and institution or investor/intermediary and fund manager.

3.name: AdvRefID
3.desc: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types.

6.name: AvgPx
6.desc: Calculated average price of all fills on this order.

7.name: BeginSeqNo
7.desc: Message sequence number of first message in range to be resent

8.name: BeginString
8.desc: Identifies beginning of new message and protocol version. ALWAYS FIRST FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

9.name: BodyLength
9.desc: Message length, in bytes, is verified by counting the number of characters in the message following the BodyLength (9) field up to, and including, the delimiter immediately preceding the CheckSum (10) field.

10.name: CheckSum
10.desc: Three byte, simple checksum (see Volume 2: "CheckSum Calculation" for description). ALWAYS LAST FIELD IN MESSAGE; i.e. serves, with the trailing <SOH>, as the end-of-message delimiter. Always defined as three characters. (Always unencrypted)

11.name: ClOrdID
11.desc: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by the buy-side (institution, broker, intermediary etc.) (identified by SenderCompID (49) or OnBehalfOfCompID (5) as appropriate). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms, particularly those which electronically submit multi-day orders, trade globally or throughout market close periods, should ensure uniqueness across days, for example by embedding a date within the ClOrdID field.

12.name: Commission
12.desc: Commission. Note if CommType (13) is percentage, Commission of 5% should be represented as .05.

14.name: CumQty
14.desc: Total quantity (e.g. number of shares) filled.

15.name: Currency
15.desc: Identifies currency used for price. Absence of this field is interpreted as the default for the security. It is recommended that systems provide the currency value whenever possible. See " Appendix 6-A: Valid Currency Codes " for information on obtaining valid values.

16.name: EndSeqNo
16.desc: Message sequence number of last message in range to be resent. If request is for a single message BeginSeqNo (7) = EndSeqNo. If request is for all messages subsequent to a particular message, EndSeqNo = "0" (representing infinity).

17.name: ExecID
17.desc: Unique identifier of Execution Report (8) message as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN) (will be 0 (zero) for ExecType (150) =I (Order Status)).

18.name: ExecInst
18.desc: Instructions for order handling on exchange trading floor. If more than one instruction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space. *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" *** (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

19.name: ExecRefID
19.desc: Reference identifier used with Trade Cancel and Trade Correct execution types.

21.name: HandlInst
21.desc: Instructions for order handling on Broker trading floor

22.name: SecurityIDSource
22.desc: Identifies class or source of the SecurityID (48) value. Required if SecurityID is specified.

26.name: IOIRefID
26.desc: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE, transaction types.

27.name: IOIQty
27.desc: Quantity (e.g. number of shares) in numeric form or relative size.

30.name: LastMkt
30.desc: Market of execution for last fill, or an indication of the market where an order was routed

32.name: LastQty
32.desc: Quantity (e.g. shares) bought/sold on this (last) fill.

33.name: NoLinesOfText
33.desc: Identifies number of lines of text body

35.name: MsgType
35.desc: Defines message type ALWAYS THIRD FIELD IN MESSAGE. (Always unencrypted)

37.name: OrderID
37.desc: Unique identifier for Order as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which accept multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the OrderID field to assure uniqueness across days.

38.name: OrderQty
38.desc: Quantity ordered. This represents the number of shares for equities or par, face or nominal value for FI instruments.

39.name: OrdStatus
39.desc: Identifies current status of order. *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" *** (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

40.name: OrdType
40.desc: Order type. *** SOME VALUES ARE NO LONGER USED - See "Deprecated (Phased-out) Features and Supported Approach" *** (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

41.name: OrigClOrdID
41.desc: ClOrdID (11) of the previous order (NOT the initial order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous order in cancel and cancel/replace requests.

42.name: OrigTime
42.desc: "Time of message origination (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT"))"

43.name: PossDupFlag
43.desc: Indicates possible retransmission of message with this sequence number

44.name: Price
44.desc: Price per unit of quantity (e.g. per share)

48.name: SecurityID
48.desc: Security identifier value of SecurityIDSource (22) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityIDSource (22) .

49.name: SenderCompID
49.desc: Assigned value used to identify firm sending message.

50.name: SenderSubID
50.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (desk, trader, etc.)

52.name: SendingTime
52.desc: Time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

54.name: Side
54.desc: Side of order (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

55.name: Symbol
55.desc: Ticker symbol. Common, "human understood" representation of the security. SecurityID (48) value can be specified if no symbol exists (e.g. non-exchange traded Collective Investment Vehicles)

56.name: TargetCompID
56.desc: Assigned value used to identify receiving firm.

57.name: TargetSubID
57.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific individual or unit intended to receive message. "ADMIN" reserved for administrative messages not intended for a specific user.

59.name: TimeInForce
59.desc: Specifies how long the order remains in effect. Absence of this field is interpreted as DAY. NOTE not applicable to CIV Orders. (see Volume : "Glossary" for value definitions)

60.name: TransactTime
60.desc: Time of execution/order creation (expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

62.name: ValidUntilTime
62.desc: Indicates expiration time of indication message (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

63.name: SettlType
63.desc: Indicates order settlement period. If present, SettlDate (64) overrides this field. If both SettlType (63) and SettlDate (64) are omitted, the default for SettlType (63) . is 0 (Regular)

64.name: SettlDate
64.desc: Specific date of trade settlement (SettlementDate) in YYYYMMDD format.

65.name: SymbolSfx
65.desc: Additional information about the security (e.g. preferred, warrants, etc.). Note also see SecurityType (167) .

66.name: ListID
66.desc: Unique identifier for list as assigned by institution, used to associate multiple individual orders. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day. Firms which generate multi-day orders should consider embedding a date within the ListID field to assure uniqueness across days.

67.name: ListSeqNo
67.desc: Sequence of individual order within list (i.e. ListSeqNo of TotNoOrders (68) , 2 of 25, 3 of 25, . . . )

68.name: TotNoOrders
68.desc: Total number of list order entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoOrders (73) in each message that has repeating list order entries related to the same ListID (66) . Used to support fragmentation.

69.name: ListExecInst
69.desc: Free format text message containing list handling and execution instructions.

70.name: AllocID
70.desc: Unique identifier for Allocation Instruction (J) message.

71.name: AllocTransType
71.desc: Identifies allocation transaction type *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***

72.name: RefAllocID
72.desc: Reference identifier to be used with AllocTransType (71) = Replace or Cancel.

73.name: NoOrders
73.desc: Indicates number of orders to be combined for average pricing and allocation.

74.name: AvgPxPrecision
74.desc: Indicates number of decimal places to be used for average pricing. Absence of this field indicates that default precision arranged by the broker/institution is to be used.

75.name: TradeDate
75.desc: Indicates date of trade referenced in this message in YYYYMMDD format. Absence of this field indicates current day (expressed in local time at place of trade).

77.name: PositionEffect
77.desc: Indicates whether the resulting position after a trade should be an opening position or closing position. Used for omnibus accounting - where accounts are held on a gross basis instead of being netted together.

78.name: NoAllocs
78.desc: Number of repeating AllocAccount (79) / AllocPrice (366) entries.

80.name: AllocQty
80.desc: Quantity to be allocated to specific sub-account

81.name: ProcessCode
81.desc: Processing code for sub-account. Absence of this field in AllocAccount (79) / AllocPrice (366) / AllocQty (80) / ProcessCode (81) instance indicates regular trade.

82.name: NoRpts
82.desc: Total number of reports within series.

83.name: RptSeq
83.desc: Sequence number of message within report series. Used to carry reporting sequence number of the fill as represented on the Trade Report Side.

84.name: CxlQty
84.desc: Total quantity canceled for this order.

85.name: NoDlvyInst
85.desc: Number of delivery instruction fields in repeating group.

93.name: SignatureLength
93.desc: Number of bytes in signature field.

95.name: RawDataLength
95.desc: Number of bytes in raw data field.

96.name: RawData
96.desc: Unformatted raw data, can include bitmaps, word processor documents, etc.

97.name: PossResend
97.desc: Indicates that message may contain information that has been sent under another sequence number.

99.name: StopPx
99.desc: Price per unit of quantity (e.g. per share)

100.name: ExDestination
100.desc: Execution destination as defined by institution when order is entered.

102.name: CxlRejReason
102.desc: Code to identify reason for cancel rejection.

103.name: OrdRejReason
103.desc: Code to identify reason for order rejection. Note: Values 3, 4, and 5 will be used when rejecting an order due to pre-allocation information errors.

106.name: Issuer
106.desc: Name of security issuer (e.g. International Business Machines, GNMA).

110.name: MinQty
110.desc: Minimum quantity of an order to be executed.

111.name: MaxFloor
111.desc: Deprecated in FIX.5.0 The quantity to be displayed . Required for reserve orders. On orders specifies the qty to be displayed, on execution reports the currently displayed quantity.

112.name: TestReqID
112.desc: Identifier included in Test Request message to be returned in resulting Heartbeat

113.name: ReportToExch
113.desc: Identifies party of trade responsible for exchange reporting.

114.name: LocateReqd
114.desc: Indicates whether the broker is to locate the stock in conjunction with a short sell order.

115.name: OnBehalfOfCompID
115.desc: Assigned value used to identify firm originating message if the message was delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the SenderCompID field and the firm originating the message in this field.

116.name: OnBehalfOfSubID
116.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator (i.e. trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

118.name: NetMoney
118.desc: Total amount due as the result of the transaction (e.g. for Buy order - principal + commission + fees) reported in currency of execution.

119.name: SettlCurrAmt
119.desc: Total amount due expressed in settlement currency (includes the effect of the forex transaction)

121.name: ForexReq
121.desc: Indicates request for forex accommodation trade to be executed along with security transaction.

122.name: OrigSendingTime
122.desc: Original time of message transmission (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT") when transmitting orders as the result of a resend request.

123.name: GapFillFlag
123.desc: Indicates that the Sequence Reset message is replacing administrative or application messages which will not be resent.

124.name: NoExecs
124.desc: No of execution repeating group entries to follow.

126.name: ExpireTime
126.desc: Time/Date of order expiration (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT").

128.name: DeliverToCompID
128.desc: Assigned value used to identify the firm targeted to receive the message if the message is delivered by a third party i.e. the third party firm identifier would be delivered in the TargetCompID (56) field and the ultimate receiver firm ID in this field.

129.name: DeliverToSubID
129.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient (i.e. trader) if the message is delivered by a third party

130.name: IOINaturalFlag
130.desc: Indicates that IOI is the result of an existing agency order or a facilitation position resulting from an agency order, not from principal trading or order solicitation activity.

136.name: NoMiscFees
136.desc: Number of repeating groups of miscellaneous fees

141.name: ResetSeqNumFlag
141.desc: Indicates that the both sides of the FIX session should reset sequence numbers.

142.name: SenderLocationID
142.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

143.name: TargetLocationID
143.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message destination's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader)

144.name: OnBehalfOfLocationID
144.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message originator's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

145.name: DeliverToLocationID
145.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific message recipient's location (i.e. geographic location and/or desk, trader) if the message was delivered by a third party

146.name: NoRelatedSym
146.desc: Specifies the number of repeating symbols specified.

147.name: Subject
147.desc: The subject of an Email message

148.name: Headline
148.desc: The headline of a News message

149.name: URLLink
149.desc: A URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) or URL (Uniform Resource Locator) link to additional information (i.e. http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uniform_Resource_Locator)

150.name: ExecType
150.desc: Describes the specific Execution Report (i.e. Pending Cancel) while OrdStatus (39) will always identify the current order status (i.e. Partially Filled) *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***

151.name: LeavesQty
151.desc: Quantity open for further execution. If the OrdStatus (39) is Canceled, DoneForTheDay, Expired, Calculated, or Rejected (in which case the order is no longer active) then LeavesQty could be 0, otherwise LeavesQty = OrderQty (38) - CumQty (14) .

152.name: CashOrderQty
152.desc: Specifies the approximate order quantity desired in total monetary units vs. as tradeable units (e.g. number of shares). The broker or fund manager (for CIV orders) would be responsible for converting and calculating a tradeable unit (e.g. share) quantity ( OrderQty (38) ) based upon this amount to be used for the actual order and subsequent messages.

155.name: SettlCurrFxRate
155.desc: Foreign exchange rate used to compute SettlCurrAmt (119) from Currency (15) to SettlCurrency (120)

156.name: SettlCurrFxRateCalc
156.desc: Specifies whether or not SettlCurrFxRate (155) should be multiplied or divided.

157.name: NumDaysInterest
157.desc: Number of Days of Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income. Note value may be negative.

158.name: AccruedInterestRate
158.desc: The amount the buyer compensates the seller for the portion of the next coupon interest payment the seller has earned but will not receive from the issuer because the issuer will send the next coupon payment to the buyer. Accrued Interest Rate is the annualized Accrued Interest amount divided by the purchase price of the bond.

159.name: AccruedInterestAmt
159.desc: Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income

160.name: SettlInstMode
160.desc: Indicates mode used for Settlement Instructions message. *** SOME VALUES HAVE BEEN REPLACED - See "Replaced Features and Supported Approach" ***

161.name: AllocText
161.desc: Free format text related to a specific AllocAccount (79).

164.name: EmailThreadID
164.desc: Unique identifier for an email thread (new and chain of replies)

167.name: SecurityType
167.desc: Indicates type of security. See also the Product (460) and CFICode (461) fields. It is recommended that CFICode be used instead of SecurityType for non-Fixed Income instruments.

168.name: EffectiveTime
168.desc: Time the details within the message should take effect (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

169.name: StandInstDbType
169.desc: Identifies the Standing Instruction database used

170.name: StandInstDbName
170.desc: Name of the Standing Instruction database represented with StandInstDbType (169) (i.e. the Global Custodians name).

171.name: StandInstDbID
171.desc: Unique identifier used on the Standing Instructions database for the Standing Instructions to be referenced.

189.name: BidForwardPoints
189.desc: Bid F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

191.name: OfferForwardPoints
191.desc: Offer F/X forward points added to spot rate. May be a negative value.

192.name: OrderQty2
192.desc: Deprecated in FIX.5.0 OrderQty (38) of the future part of a F/X swap order.

193.name: SettlDate2
193.desc: Deprecated in FIX.5.0 SettlDate (64) of the future part of a F/X swap order.

195.name: LastForwardPoints
195.desc: F/X forward points added to LastSpotRate (194) . May be a negative value. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

196.name: AllocLinkID
196.desc: Can be used to link two different Allocation messages (each with unique AllocID (70) ) together, i.e. for F/X "Netting" or "Swaps". Should be unique.

197.name: AllocLinkType
197.desc: Identifies the type of Allocation linkage when AllocLinkID (196) ,is used.

198.name: SecondaryOrderID
198.desc: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the OrderID (37) used by an exchange or executing system.

199.name: NoIOIQualifiers
199.desc: Number of repeating groups of IOIQualifier (104) s.

200.name: MaturityMonthYear
200.desc: Can be used with standardized derivatives vs. the MaturityDate (541) field. Month and Year of the maturity (used for standardized futures and options).

201.name: PutOrCall
201.desc: Indicates whether an Option is for a put or call.

203.name: CoveredOrUncovered
203.desc: Used for derivative products, such as options

206.name: OptAttribute
206.desc: Can be used for SecurityType (167) =OPT to identify a particular security.

207.name: SecurityExchange
207.desc: Market used to help identify a security.

208.name: NotifyBrokerOfCredit
208.desc: Indicates whether or not details should be communicated to BrokerOfCredit (i.e. step-in broker).

209.name: AllocHandlInst
209.desc: Indicates how the receiver (i.e. third party) of Allocation message should handle/process the account details.

210.name: MaxShow
210.desc: Deprecated in FIX.5.0 Maximum quantity (e.g. number of shares) within an order to be shown to other customers (i.e. sent via an IOI).

211.name: PegOffsetValue
211.desc: Amount (signed) added to the peg for a pegged order in the context of the PegOffsetType (836)

212.name: XmlDataLen
212.desc: Length of the XmlData data block.

213.name: XmlData
213.desc: Actual XML data stream (e.g. FIXML). See approriate XML reference (e.g. FIXML). Note: may contain embedded SOH characters.

214.name: SettlInstRefID
214.desc: Reference identifier for the SettlInstID (162) with Cancel and Replace SettlInstTransType (163) transaction types.

215.name: NoRoutingIDs
215.desc: Number of repeating groups of RoutingID (217) and RoutingType (216) values.

216.name: RoutingType
216.desc: Indicates the type of RoutingID (217) specified.

217.name: RoutingID
217.desc: Assigned value used to identify a specific routing destination.

218.name: Spread
218.desc: For Fixed Income. Either Swap Spread or Spread to Benchmark depending upon the order type.

220.name: BenchmarkCurveCurrency
220.desc: Identifies currency used for benchmark curve. See " Appendix 6-A: Valid Currency Codes " for information on obtaining valid values.

222.name: BenchmarkCurvePoint
222.desc: Point on benchmark curve. Free form values: e.g. "Y", "7Y", "INTERPOLATED".

223.name: CouponRate
223.desc: The rate of interest that, when multiplied by the principal, par value, or face value of a bond, provides the currency amount of the periodic interest payment. The coupon is always cited, along with maturity, in any quotation of a bond's price.

224.name: CouponPaymentDate
224.desc: Date interest is to be paid. Used in identifying Corporate Bond issues.

225.name: IssueDate
225.desc: The date on which a bond or stock offering is issued. It may or may not be the same as the effective date ("Dated Date") or the date on which interest begins to accrue ("Interest Accrual Date")

226.name: RepurchaseTerm
226.desc: Deprecated in FIX.4.4 Number of business days before repurchase of a repo. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

227.name: RepurchaseRate
227.desc: Deprecated in FIX.4.4 Percent of par at which a Repo will be repaid. Represented as a percent, e.g. .9525 represents 95-/4 percent of par. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

228.name: Factor
228.desc: For Fixed Income: Amorization Factor for deriving Current face from Original face for ABS or MBS securities, note the fraction may be greater than, equal to or less than 1. In TIPS securities this is the Inflation index.

229.name: TradeOriginationDate
229.desc: Used with Fixed Income for Muncipal New Issue Market. Agreement in principal between counter-parties prior to actual trade date.

230.name: ExDate
230.desc: The date when a distribution of interest is deducted from a securities assets or set aside for payment to bondholders. On the ex-date, the securities price drops by the amount of the distribution (plus or minus any market activity).

231.name: ContractMultiplier
231.desc: Specifies the ratio or multiply factor to convert from "nominal" units (e.g. contracts) to total units (e.g. shares) (e.g. 1.0, 100, 1000, etc). Applicable For Fixed Income, Convertible Bonds, Derivatives, etc.

234.name: StipulationValue
234.desc: For Fixed Income. Value of stipulation.

235.name: YieldType
235.desc: Type of yield. (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

237.name: TotalTakedown
237.desc: The price at which the securities are distributed to the different members of an underwriting group for the primary market in Municipals, total gross underwriter's spread.

238.name: Concession
238.desc: Provides the reduction in price for the secondary market in Muncipals.

239.name: RepoCollateralSecurityType
239.desc: Identifies the collateral used in the transaction.

240.name: RedemptionDate
240.desc: Deprecated in FIX.4.4 Return of investor's principal in a security. Bond redemption can occur before maturity date.(Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

243.name: UnderlyingRepoCollateralSecurityType
243.desc: Deprecated in FIX.4.4 Underlying security's RepoCollateralSecurityType. See RepoCollateralSecurityType (239) field for description.(Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

244.name: UnderlyingRepurchaseTerm
244.desc: Deprecated in FIX.4.4 Underlying security's RepurchaseTerm. See RepurchaseTerm (226) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

245.name: UnderlyingRepurchaseRate
245.desc: Deprecated in FIX.4.4 Underlying security's RepurchaseRate. See RepurchaseRate (227) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

247.name: UnderlyingRedemptionDate
247.desc: Deprecated in FIX.4.4 Underlying security's RedemptionDate. See RedemptionDate (240) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

248.name: LegCouponPaymentDate
248.desc: Multileg instrument's individual leg securitys CouponPaymentDate.

249.name: LegIssueDate
249.desc: Multileg instrument's individual leg securitys IssueDate.

250.name: LegRepoCollateralSecurityType
250.desc: Deprecated in FIX.4.4 Multileg instrument's individual leg security's RepoCollateralSecurityType. See RepoCollateralSecurityType (239) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

251.name: LegRepurchaseTerm
251.desc: Deprecated in FIX.4.4 Multileg instrument's individual leg security?s RepurchaseTerm. See RepurchaseTerm (226) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

252.name: LegRepurchaseRate
252.desc: Deprecated in FIX.4.4 Multileg instrument's individual leg security's RepurchaseRate. See RepurchaseRate (227) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

253.name: LegFactor
253.desc: Multileg instrument's individual leg securitys Factor.

254.name: LegRedemptionDate
254.desc: Deprecated in FIX.4.4 Multileg instrument's individual leg security's RedemptionDate. See RedemptionDate (240) field for description (Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3) (prior to FIX 4.4 field was of type UTCDate)

255.name: CreditRating
255.desc: An evaluation of a company's ability to repay obligations or its likelihood of not defaulting. These evaluation are provided by Credit Rating Agencies, i.e. S&P, Moody's.

257.name: LegCreditRating
257.desc: Multileg instrument's individual leg securitys CreditRating.

258.name: TradedFlatSwitch
258.desc: Driver and part of trade in the event that the Security Master file was wrong at the point of entry(Note tag # was reserved in FIX 4.1, added in FIX 4.3)

259.name: BasisFeatureDate
259.desc: BasisFeatureDate allows requesting firms within fixed income the ability to request an alternative yield-to-worst, -maturity, -extended or other call. This flows through the confirm process.

262.name: MDReqID
262.desc: Unique identifier for Market Data Request

264.name: MarketDepth
264.desc: Depth of market for Book Snapshot

265.name: MDUpdateType
265.desc: Specifies the type of Market Data update.

266.name: AggregatedBook
266.desc: Specifies whether or not book entries should be aggregated. (Not specified) = broker option

268.name: NoMDEntries
268.desc: Number of entries in Market Data message.

270.name: MDEntryPx
270.desc: Price of the Market Data Entry.

271.name: MDEntrySize
271.desc: Quantity or volume represented by the Market Data Entry.

275.name: MDMkt
275.desc: Deprecated in FIX.5.0 Market posting quote / trade.

276.name: QuoteCondition
276.desc: Space-delimited list of conditions describing a quote.

277.name: TradeCondition
277.desc: Space-delimited list of conditions describing a trade

279.name: MDUpdateAction
279.desc: Type of Market Data update action.

281.name: MDReqRejReason
281.desc: Reason for the rejection of a Market Data Request (V) .

282.name: MDEntryOriginator
282.desc: Deprecated in FIX.5.0 Originator of a Market Data Entry

283.name: LocationID
283.desc: Identification of a Market Makers location

284.name: DeskID
284.desc: Identification of a Market Makers desk

286.name: OpenCloseSettlFlag
286.desc: Flag that identifies a market data entry. (Prior to FIX 4.3 this field was of type char)

287.name: SellerDays
287.desc: Specifies the number of days that may elapse before delivery of the security

290.name: MDEntryPositionNo
290.desc: Display position of a bid or offer, numbered from most competitive to least competitive, per market side, beginning with .

291.name: FinancialStatus
291.desc: Identifies a firm's or a security's financial status

292.name: CorporateAction
292.desc: Identifies the type of Corporate Action.

295.name: NoQuoteEntries
295.desc: The number of quote entries for a QuoteSet.

296.name: NoQuoteSets
296.desc: The number of sets of quotes in the message.

297.name: QuoteStatus
297.desc: Identifies the status of the quote acknowledgement.

298.name: QuoteCancelType
298.desc: Identifies the type of quote cancel.

299.name: QuoteEntryID
299.desc: Uniquely identifies the quote as part of a QuoteSet.

301.name: QuoteResponseLevel
301.desc: Level of Response requested from receiver of quote messages.

303.name: QuoteRequestType
303.desc: Indicates the type of Quote Request being generated

304.name: TotNoQuoteEntries
304.desc: Total number of quotes for the QuoteSet across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoQuoteEntries (295) in each message that has repeating quotes that are part of the same QuoteSet.

308.name: UnderlyingSecurityExchange
308.desc: Underlying securitys SecurityExchange. Can be used to identify the underlying security.

313.name: UnderlyingMaturityMonthYear
313.desc: Underlying securitys MaturityMonthYear. Can be used with standardized derivatives vs. the UnderlyingMaturityDate (542) field.

320.name: SecurityReqID
320.desc: Unique ID of a Security Definition Request.

322.name: SecurityResponseID
322.desc: Unique ID of a Security Definition message.

323.name: SecurityResponseType
323.desc: Type of Security Definition message response.

324.name: SecurityStatusReqID
324.desc: Unique ID of a Security Status Request message.

325.name: UnsolicitedIndicator
325.desc: Indicates whether or not message is being sent as a result of a subscription request or not.

326.name: SecurityTradingStatus
326.desc: Identifies the trading status applicable to the transaction.

327.name: HaltReason
327.desc: Denotes the reason for the Opening Delay or Trading Halt.

328.name: InViewOfCommon
328.desc: Indicates whether or not the halt was due to Common Stock trading being halted.

329.name: DueToRelated
329.desc: Indicates whether or not the halt was due to the Related Security being halted.

332.name: HighPx
332.desc: Represents an indication of the high end of the price range for a security prior to the open or reopen.

333.name: LowPx
333.desc: Represents an indication of the low end of the price range for a security prior to the open or reopen.

335.name: TradSesReqID
335.desc: Unique ID of a Trading Session Status message.

337.name: ContraTrader
337.desc: Identifies the trader (e.g. "badge number") of the ContraBroker.

341.name: TradSesStartTime
341.desc: Starting time of the trading session

342.name: TradSesOpenTime
342.desc: Time of the opening of the trading session

343.name: TradSesPreCloseTime
343.desc: Time of the pre-closed of the trading session

344.name: TradSesCloseTime
344.desc: Closing time of the trading session

345.name: TradSesEndTime
345.desc: End time of the trading session

346.name: NumberOfOrders
346.desc: Number of orders in the market.

347.name: MessageEncoding
347.desc: Type of message encoding (non-ASCII (non-English) characters) used in a messages "Encoded" fields.

348.name: EncodedIssuerLen
348.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedIssuer (349) field.

349.name: EncodedIssuer
349.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Issuer field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Issuer (106) field.

350.name: EncodedSecurityDescLen
350.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedSecurityDesc (351) field.

351.name: EncodedSecurityDesc
351.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the SecurityDesc (107) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the SecurityDesc (107) field.

352.name: EncodedListExecInstLen
352.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListExecInst (353) field.

353.name: EncodedListExecInst
353.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListExecInst (69) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListExecInst field.

354.name: EncodedTextLen
354.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedText (355) field.

355.name: EncodedText
355.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Text (58) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Text field.

356.name: EncodedSubjectLen
356.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedSubject (357) field.

357.name: EncodedSubject
357.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Subject (147) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Subject field.

358.name: EncodedHeadlineLen
358.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedHeadline (359) , field.

359.name: EncodedHeadline
359.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the Headline (148) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the Headline field.

360.name: EncodedAllocTextLen
360.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedAllocText (361) field.

361.name: EncodedAllocText
361.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the AllocText (161) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the AllocText field.

362.name: EncodedUnderlyingIssuerLen
362.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingIssuer (363) field.

363.name: EncodedUnderlyingIssuer
363.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingIssuer (306) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingIssuer field.

364.name: EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDescLen
364.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc (365) field.

365.name: EncodedUnderlyingSecurityDesc
365.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the UnderlyingSecurityDesc (307) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the UnderlyingSecurityeDesc field.

366.name: AllocPrice
366.desc: Executed price for an AllocAccount (79) entry used when using "executed price" vs. "average price" allocations (e.g. Japan).

367.name: QuoteSetValidUntilTime
367.desc: Indicates expiration time of this particular QuoteSet (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT").

369.name: LastMsgSeqNumProcessed
369.desc: The last MsgSeqNum (34) value received by the FIX engine and processed by downstream application, such as trading engine or order routing system. Can be specified on every message sent. Useful for detecting a backlog with a counterparty.

371.name: RefTagID
371.desc: The tag number of the FIX field being referenced.

372.name: RefMsgType
372.desc: The MsgType (35) of the FIX message being referenced.

373.name: SessionRejectReason
373.desc: Code to identify reason for a session-level Reject message.

374.name: BidRequestTransType
374.desc: Identifies the Bid Request message type.

375.name: ContraBroker
375.desc: Identifies contra broker. Standard NASD market-maker mnemonic is preferred.

376.name: ComplianceID
376.desc: ID used to represent this transaction for compliance purposes (e.g. OATS reporting).

377.name: SolicitedFlag
377.desc: Indicates whether or not the order was solicited.

378.name: ExecRestatementReason
378.desc: Code to identify reason for an Execution Report message sent with ExecType=Restated or used when communicating an unsolicited cancel.

379.name: BusinessRejectRefID
379.desc: The value of the business-level "ID" field on the message being referenced.

380.name: BusinessRejectReason
380.desc: Code to identify reason for a Business Message Reject message.

381.name: GrossTradeAmt
381.desc: Total amount traded (e.g. CumQty (14) * AvgPx (6) ) expressed in units of currency. For FX Futures this is used to express the notional value of a fill when LastQty and other quantity fields are express in terms of contract size.

383.name: MaxMessageSize
383.desc: Maximum number of bytes supported for a single message.

384.name: NoMsgTypes
384.desc: Number of MsgType (35) in repeating group.

385.name: MsgDirection
385.desc: Specifies the direction of the messsage.

386.name: NoTradingSessions
386.desc: Number of TradingSessionID (336) in repeating group.

388.name: DiscretionInst
388.desc: Code to identify the price a DiscretionOffsetValue (389) is related to and should be mathematically added to.

389.name: DiscretionOffsetValue
389.desc: Amount (signed) added to the "related to" price specified via DiscretionInst (388) , in the context of DiscretionOffsetType (842) .

390.name: BidID
390.desc: Unique identifier for Bid Response as assigned by sell-side (broker, exchange, ECN). Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

391.name: ClientBidID
391.desc: Unique identifier for a Bid Request as assigned by institution. Uniqueness must be guaranteed within a single trading day.

394.name: BidType
394.desc: Code to identify the type of Bid Request.

399.name: BidDescriptorType
399.desc: Code to identify the type of BidDescriptor (400) .

400.name: BidDescriptor
400.desc: BidDescriptor (400) value. Usage depends upon BidDescriptorType (399) .

401.name: SideValueInd
401.desc: Code to identify which "SideValue" the value refers to. SideValue1 and SideValue2 are used as opposed to Buy or Sell so that the basket can be quoted either way as Buy or Sell.

402.name: LiquidityPctLow
402.desc: Liquidity indicator or lower limit if TotNoRelatedSym (393) > 1. Represented as a percentage.

403.name: LiquidityPctHigh
403.desc: Upper liquidity indicator if TotNoRelatedSym (393) > 1. Represented as a percentage.

404.name: LiquidityValue
404.desc: Value between LiquidityPctLow (402) and LiquidityPctHigh (403) in Currency

405.name: EFPTrackingError
405.desc: Eg Used in EFP trades 2% (EFP Exchange for Physical ). Represented as a percentage.

407.name: OutsideIndexPct
407.desc: Used in EFP trades. Represented as a percentage.

409.name: LiquidityIndType
409.desc: Code to identify the type of liquidity indicator.

410.name: WtAverageLiquidity
410.desc: Overall weighted average liquidity expressed as a % of average daily volume. Represented as a percentage.

411.name: ExchangeForPhysical
411.desc: Indicates whether or not to exchange for phsyical.

413.name: CrossPercent
413.desc: Percentage of program that crosses in Currency. Represented as a percentage.

414.name: ProgRptReqs
414.desc: Code to identify the desired frequency of progress reports.

415.name: ProgPeriodInterval
415.desc: Time in minutes between each ListStatus report sent by SellSide. Zero means dont send status.

416.name: IncTaxInd
416.desc: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

417.name: NumBidders
417.desc: Indicates the total number of bidders on the list

418.name: BidTradeType
418.desc: Code to represent the type of trade.

419.name: BasisPxType
419.desc: Code to represent the basis price type.

420.name: NoBidComponents
420.desc: Indicates the number of list entries.

422.name: TotNoStrikes
422.desc: Total number of strike price entries across all messages. Should be the sum of all NoStrikes (428) in each message that has repeating strike price entries related to the same ListID (66) . Used to support fragmentation.

423.name: PriceType
423.desc: Code to represent the price type.

424.name: DayOrderQty
424.desc: For GT orders, the OrderQty (38) less all quantity (adjusted for stock splits) that traded on previous days. DayOrderQty (424) = OrderQty (38) - ( CumQty (14) - DayCumQty (425) )

425.name: DayCumQty
425.desc: Quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

426.name: DayAvgPx
426.desc: The average price for quantity on a GT order that has traded today.

427.name: GTBookingInst
427.desc: Code to identify whether to book out executions on a part-filled GT order on the day of execution or to accumulate.

428.name: NoStrikes
428.desc: Number of list strike price entries.

429.name: ListStatusType
429.desc: Code to represent the status type.

430.name: NetGrossInd
430.desc: Code to represent whether value is net (inclusive of tax) or gross.

431.name: ListOrderStatus
431.desc: Code to represent the status of a list order.

432.name: ExpireDate
432.desc: Date of order expiration (last day the order can trade), always expressed in terms of the local market date. The time at which the order expires is determined by the local markets business practices

434.name: CxlRejResponseTo
434.desc: Identifies the type of request that a Order Cancel Reject (9) is in response to.

435.name: UnderlyingCouponRate
435.desc: Underlying securitys CouponRate. See CouponRate (223) field for description

436.name: UnderlyingContractMultiplier
436.desc: Underlying securitys ContractMultiplier. See ContractMultiplier (231) field for description

438.name: ContraTradeTime
438.desc: Identifes the time of the trade with the ContraBroker (375) . (always expressed in UTC (Universal Time Coordinated, also known as "GMT")

441.name: LiquidityNumSecurities
441.desc: Number of Securites between LiquidityPctLow (402) and LiquidityPctHigh (403) in Currency.

442.name: MultiLegReportingType
442.desc: Used to indicate what an Execution Report represents (e.g. used with multi-leg securities, such as option strategies, spreads, etc.).

443.name: StrikeTime
443.desc: The time at which current market prices are used to determine the value of a basket.

444.name: ListStatusText
444.desc: Free format text string related to List Status.

445.name: EncodedListStatusTextLen
445.desc: Byte length of encoded (non-ASCII characters) EncodedListStatusText (446) field.

446.name: EncodedListStatusText
446.desc: Encoded (non-ASCII characters) representation of the ListStatusText (444) field in the encoded format specified via the MessageEncoding (347) field. If used, the ASCII (English) representation should also be specified in the ListStatusText field.

447.name: PartyIDSource
447.desc: Identifies class or source of the PartyID (448) value. Required if PartyID is specified. Note: applicable values depend upon PartyRole (452) specified.

448.name: PartyID
448.desc: Party identifier/code. See PartyIDSource (447) and PartyRole (452) .

451.name: NetChgPrevDay
451.desc: Net change from previous days closing price vs. last traded price.

452.name: PartyRole
452.desc: Identifies the type or role of the PartyID (448) specified.

453.name: NoPartyIDs
453.desc: Number of PartyID (448) , PartyIDSource (447) , and PartyRole (452) entries

455.name: SecurityAltID
455.desc: Alternate Security identifier value for this security of SecurityAltIDSource (456) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires SecurityAltIDSource (456) .

456.name: SecurityAltIDSource
456.desc: Identifies class or source of the SecurityAltID (455) value. Required if SecurityAltID (455) is specified.

458.name: UnderlyingSecurityAltID
458.desc: Alternate Security identifier value for this underlying security of UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource (459) type (e.g. CUSIP, SEDOL, ISIN, etc). Requires UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource.

459.name: UnderlyingSecurityAltIDSource
459.desc: Identifies class or source of the UnderlyingSecurityAltID (458) value. Required if UnderlyingSecurityAltID (458) is specified.

460.name: Product
460.desc: Indicates the type of product the security is associated with. See also the CFICode (461) and SecurityType (167) fields.

461.name: CFICode
461.desc: Indicates the type of security using ISO 10962 standard, Classification of Financial Instruments (CFI code) values. ISO 10962 is maintained by ANNA (Association of National Numbering Agencies) acting as Registration Authority. See " Appendix 6-B FIX Fields Based Upon Other Standards ". See also the Product (460) and SecurityType (167) fields. It is recommended that CFICode be used instead of SecurityType (167) for non-Fixed Income instruments.

464.name: TestMessageIndicator
464.desc: Indicates whether or not this FIX Session is a "test" vs. "production" connection. Useful for preventing "accidents".

466.name: BookingRefID
466.desc: Common reference passed to a post-trade booking process (e.g. industry matching utility).

467.name: IndividualAllocID
467.desc: Unique identifier for a specific NoAllocs (78) repeating group instance (e.g. for an AllocAccount).

468.name: RoundingDirection
468.desc: Specifies which direction to round For CIV indicates whether or not the quantity of shares/units is to be rounded and in which direction where CashOrderQty (152) or (for CIV only) OrderPercent (516) are specified on an order.

469.name: RoundingModulus
469.desc: For CIV - a float value indicating the value to which rounding is required.

470.name: CountryOfIssue
470.desc: ISO Country code of instrument issue (e.g. the country portion typically used in ISIN). Can be used in conjunction with non-ISIN SecurityID (48) (e.g. CUSIP for Municipal Bonds without ISIN) to provide uniqueness.

471.name: StateOrProvinceOfIssue
471.desc: A two-character state or province abbreviation.

472.name: LocaleOfIssue
472.desc: Identifies the locale. For Municipal Security Issuers other than state or province. Refer to

473.name: NoRegistDtls
473.desc: The number of registration details on a Registration Instructions message

474.name: MailingDtls
474.desc: Set of Correspondence address details, possibly including phone, fax, etc.

475.name: InvestorCountryOfResidence
475.desc: The ISO 3166 Country code (2 character) identifying which country the beneficial investor is resident for tax purposes.

476.name: PaymentRef
476.desc: "Settlement Payment Reference" - A free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation, e.g. a Client and/or Order ID number.

477.name: DistribPaymentMethod
477.desc: A code identifying the payment method for a (fractional) distribution.

478.name: CashDistribCurr
478.desc: Specifies currency to be use for Cash Distributions see " Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes ".

479.name: CommCurrency
479.desc: Specifies currency to be use for Commission (12) if the Commission currency is different from the Deal Currency - see " Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes ".

480.name: CancellationRights
480.desc: For CIV A one character code identifying whether Cancellation rights/Cooling off period applies.

481.name: MoneyLaunderingStatus
481.desc: A one character code identifying Money laundering status.

482.name: MailingInst
482.desc: Free format text to specify mailing instruction requirements, e.g. "no third party mailings".

483.name: TransBkdTime
483.desc: For CIV A date and time stamp to indicate the time a CIV order was booked by the fund manager.

484.name: ExecPriceType
484.desc: For CIV - Identifies how the execution price LastPx (31) was calculated from the fund unit/share price(s) calculated at the fund valuation point.

485.name: ExecPriceAdjustment
485.desc: For CIV the amount or percentage by which the fund unit/share price was adjusted, as indicated by ExecPriceType (484)

486.name: DateOfBirth
486.desc: The date of birth applicable to the individual, e.g. required to open some types of tax-exempt account.

487.name: TradeReportTransType
487.desc: Identifies Trade Capture Report (AE) message transaction type

488.name: CardHolderName
488.desc: The name of the payment card holder as specified on the card being used for payment.

489.name: CardNumber
489.desc: The number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

490.name: CardExpDate
490.desc: The expiry date of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment.

491.name: CardIssNum
491.desc: The issue number of the payment card as specified on the card being used for payment. This is only applicable to certain types of card.

492.name: PaymentMethod
492.desc: A code identifying the Settlement payment method. 16 through 998 are reserved for future use

493.name: RegistAcctType
493.desc: For CIV a fund manager-defined code identifying which of the fund managers account types is required.

494.name: Designation
494.desc: Free format text defining the designation to be associated with a holding on the register. Used to identify assets of a specific underlying investor using a common registration, e.g. a brokers nominee or street name.

495.name: TaxAdvantageType
495.desc: For CIV - a code identifying the type of tax exempt account in which purchased shares/units are to be held.

496.name: RegistRejReasonText
496.desc: Text indicating reason(s) why a Registration Instruction has been rejected.

497.name: FundRenewWaiv
497.desc: A one character code identifying whether the Fund based renewal commission is to be waived.

498.name: CashDistribAgentName
498.desc: Name of local agent bank if for cash distributions

499.name: CashDistribAgentCode
499.desc: BIC (Bank Identification Code--Swift managed) code of agent bank for cash distributions.

500.name: CashDistribAgentAcctNumber
500.desc: Account number at agent bank for distributions.

501.name: CashDistribPayRef
501.desc: Free format Payment reference to assist with reconciliation of distributions.

502.name: CashDistribAgentAcctName
502.desc: Name of account at agent bank for distributions.

503.name: CardStartDate
503.desc: The start date of the card as specified on the card being used for payment.

504.name: PaymentDate
504.desc: The date written on a cheque or date payment should be submitted to the relevant clearing system.

505.name: PaymentRemitterID
505.desc: Identifies sender of a payment, e.g. the payment remitter or a customer reference number.

506.name: RegistStatus
506.desc: Registration status as returned by the broker or (for CIV) the fund manager.

507.name: RegistRejReasonCode
507.desc: Reason(s) why Registration Instructions (o) has been rejected.

508.name: RegistRefID
508.desc: Reference identifier for the RegistID (513) with Cancel and Replace RegistTransType (514) transaction types.

509.name: RegistDtls
509.desc: Set of Registration name and address details, possibly including phone, fax etc.

510.name: NoDistribInsts
510.desc: The number of Distribution Instructions on a Registration Instructions (o) message.

511.name: RegistEmail
511.desc: Email address relating to Registration name and address details.

512.name: DistribPercentage
512.desc: The amount of each distribution to go to this beneficiary, expressed as a percentage.

513.name: RegistID
513.desc: Unique identifier of the registration details as assigned by institution or intermediary.

515.name: ExecValuationPoint
515.desc: For CIV - a date and time stamp to indicate the fund valuation point with respect to which a order was priced by the fund manager.

516.name: OrderPercent
516.desc: For CIV specifies the approximate order quantity desired. For a CIV Sale it specifies percentage of investors total holding to be sold. For a CIV switch/exchange it specifies percentage of investors cash realised from sales to be re-invested. The executing broker, intermediary or fund manager is responsible for converting and calculating OrderQty (38) in shares/units for subsequent messages.

518.name: NoContAmts
518.desc: The number of Contract Amount details on an Execution Report (8) message.

520.name: ContAmtValue
520.desc: Value of Contract Amount, e.g. a financial amount or percentage as indicated by ContAmtType (519) .

521.name: ContAmtCurr
521.desc: Specifies currency for the Contract amount if different from the Deal Currency - see " Appendix 6-A; Valid Currency Codes ".

523.name: PartySubID
523.desc: Sub-identifier (e.g. Clearing Account for PartyRole (452) =Clearing Firm, Locate ID # for PartyRole (452) =Locate/Lending Firm, etc). Not required when using PartyID (448) , PartyIDSource (447) , and PartyRole (452) .

524.name: NestedPartyID
524.desc: PartyID value within a nested repeating group.

525.name: NestedPartyIDSource
525.desc: PartyIDSource (447) value within a nested repeating group.

526.name: SecondaryClOrdID
526.desc: Assigned by the party which originates the order. Can be used to provide the ClOrdID (11) used by an exchange or executing system.

527.name: SecondaryExecID
527.desc: Assigned by the party which accepts the order. Can be used to provide the ExecID (17) used by an exchange or executing system.

528.name: OrderCapacity
528.desc: Designates the capacity of the firm placing the order.

529.name: OrderRestrictions
529.desc: Restrictions associated with an order. If more than one restriction is applicable to an order, this field can contain multiple instructions separated by space.

530.name: MassCancelRequestType
530.desc: Specifies scope of Order Mass Cancel Request (q) .

531.name: MassCancelResponse
531.desc: Specifies the action taken by counterparty order handling system as a result of the Order Mass Cancel Request (q)

532.name: MassCancelRejectReason
532.desc: Reason Order Mass Cancel Request (q) was rejected.

533.name: TotalAffectedOrders
533.desc: Total number of orders affected by Order Mass Cancel Request (q) .

534.name: NoAffectedOrders
534.desc: Number of affected orders in the repeating group of order ids.

535.name: AffectedOrderID
535.desc: OrderID (37) of an order affected by a Order Mass Cancel Request (q) .

536.name: AffectedSecondaryOrderID
536.desc: SecondaryOrderID (198) of an order affected by a Order Mass Cancel Request (q) .

538.name: NestedPartyRole
538.desc: PartyRole (452) value within a nested repeating group.

539.name: NoNestedPartyIDs
539.desc: Number of NestedPartyID (524) , NestedPartyIDSource (525) , and NestedPartyRole (538) entries

540.name: TotalAccruedInterestAmt
540.desc: Deprecated in FIX.4.4 Total Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income.

543.name: InstrRegistry
543.desc: Values may include BIC for the depository or custodian who maintain ownership records, the ISO country code for the location of the record, or the value "ZZ" to specify physical ownership of the security (e.g. stock certificate).

544.name: CashMargin
544.desc: Identifies whether an order is a margin order or a non-margin order. This is primarily used when sending orders to Japanese exchanges to indicate sell margin or buy to cover. The same tag could be assigned also by buy-side to indicate the intent to sell or buy margin and the sell-side to accept or reject (base on some validation criteria) the margin request.

545.name: NestedPartySubID
545.desc: PartySubID (523) value within a nested repeating group.

546.name: Scope
546.desc: Specifies the market scope of the a market data.

547.name: MDImplicitDelete
547.desc: Defines how a server handles distribution of a truncated book. Defaults to broker option.

548.name: CrossID
548.desc: Identifier for a cross order. Must be unique during a given trading day. Recommend that firms use the order date as part of the CrossID for Good Till Cancel (GT) orders.

549.name: CrossType
549.desc: Type of cross being submitted to a market.

550.name: CrossPrioritization
550.desc: Indicates if one side or the other of a cross order should be prioritized.

551.name: OrigCrossID
551.desc: CrossID (548) of the previous cross order (NOT the initial cross order of the day) as assigned by the institution, used to identify the previous cross order in Cross Order Cancel Request (u) and Cross Order Cancel/Replace Request (t) .

552.name: NoSides
552.desc: Number of Side (54) repeating group instances.

555.name: NoLegs
555.desc: Number of InstrumentLeg repeating group instances.

556.name: LegCurrency
556.desc: Currency associated with a particular Leg's quantity

557.name: TotNoSecurityTypes
557.desc: Indicates total number of security types in the event that multiple Security Types (w) messages are used to return results.

558.name: NoSecurityTypes
558.desc: Number of Security Type repeating group instances.

559.name: SecurityListRequestType
559.desc: Identifies the type/criteria of Security List Request (x) .

560.name: SecurityRequestResult
560.desc: The results returned to a Security Type Request (v) message

561.name: RoundLot
561.desc: The trading lot size of a security

562.name: MinTradeVol
562.desc: The minimum trading volume for a security

563.name: MultiLegRptTypeReq
563.desc: Indicates the method of execution reporting requested by issuer of the order.

564.name: LegPositionEffect
564.desc: PositionEffect for leg of a multileg

565.name: LegCoveredOrUncovered
565.desc: CoveredOrUncovered for leg of a multileg

566.name: LegPrice
566.desc: Price for leg of a multileg

567.name: TradSesStatusRejReason
567.desc: Indicates the reason a Trading Session Status Request (g) was rejected.

570.name: PreviouslyReported
570.desc: Indicates if the trade capture report was previously reported to the counterparty

571.name: TradeReportID
571.desc: Unique identifier of Trade Capture Report (AE)

572.name: TradeReportRefID
572.desc: Reference identifier used with CANCEL and REPLACE transaction types.

573.name: MatchStatus
573.desc: The status of this trade with respect to matching or comparison.

644.name: RFQReqID

645.name: MktBidPx

646.name: MktOfferPx

648.name: MinOfferSize

649.name: QuoteStatusReqID
649.desc: Unique identifier for Quote Status Request (a) .

650.name: LegalConfirm
650.desc: Indicates that this message is to serve as the final and legal confirmation.

652.desc: The calculated or traded quantity for the underlying instrument that corresponds to a derivative. Used for transactions that include the cash instrument and the derivative.

655.name: ContraLegRefID

656.desc: Foreign exchange rate used to compute the bid SettlCurrAmt (119) from Currency (15) to SettlCurrency (120)

657.name: SettlCurrOfferFxRate
657.desc: Foreign exchange rate used to compute the offer SettlCurrAmt (119) from Currency (15) to SettlCurrency (120)

659.name: SideComplianceID

660.name: AcctIDSource
660.desc: Used to identify the source of the Account (1) code. This is especially useful if the account is a new account that the Respondent may not have setup yet in their system.

661.name: AllocAcctIDSource
661.desc: Used to identify the source of the AllocAccount (79) code.

662.name: BenchmarkPrice
662.desc: Specifies the price of the benchmark.

665.name: ConfirmStatus
665.desc: Identifies the status of the Confirmation (AK) .

667.name: ContractSettlMonth
667.desc: Specifies when the contract (i.e. MBS/TBA) will settle.

669.name: LastParPx
669.desc: Last price expressed in percent-of-par. Conditionally required for Fixed Income trades when LastPx (31) is expressed in Yield, Spread, Discount or any other type.

670.name: NoLegAllocs
670.desc: Number of Allocations for the leg

672.name: LegIndividualAllocID
672.desc: Reference for the individual allocation ticket

675.name: LegSettlCurrency
675.desc: Identifies settlement currency for the Leg.

677.name: LegBenchmarkCurveName
677.desc: Name of the Leg Benchmark Curve.

678.name: LegBenchmarkCurvePoint
678.desc: Identifies the point on the Leg Benchmark Curve.

679.name: LegBenchmarkPrice
679.desc: Used to identify the price of the benchmark security.

680.name: LegBenchmarkPriceType
680.desc: The price type of the LegBenchmarkPrice.

686.name: LegPriceType
686.desc: The price type of the LegBidPx (681) and/or LegOfferPx (684).

687.name: LegQty
687.desc: Quantity of this leg, e.g. in Quote dialog.

688.name: LegStipulationType
688.desc: For Fixed Income, type of Stipulation for this leg.

689.name: LegStipulationValue
689.desc: For Fixed Income, value of stipulation.

690.name: LegSwapType
690.desc: For Fixed Income, used instead of LegQty (687) or LegOrderQty (685) to requests the respondent to calculate the quantity based on the quantity on the opposite side of the swap.

691.name: Pool
691.desc: For Fixed Income, identifies MBS / ABS pool.

692.name: QuotePriceType
692.desc: Code to represent price type requested in Quote.

694.name: QuoteRespType
694.desc: Identifies the type of Quote Response (AJ) .

696.desc: Date to which the yield has been calculated (i.e. maturity, par call or current call, pre-refunded date).

697.name: YieldRedemptionPrice
697.desc: Price to which the yield has been calculated.

698.name: YieldRedemptionPriceType
698.desc: The price type of the YieldRedemptionPrice (697)

699.name: BenchmarkSecurityID
699.desc: The identifier of the benchmark security, e.g. Treasury against Corporate bond.

700.name: ReversalIndicator
700.desc: Indicates a trade that reverses a previous trade.

701.name: YieldCalcDate
701.desc: Include as needed to clarify yield irregularities associated with date, e.g. when it falls on a non-business day.

703.name: PosType
703.desc: Used to identify the type of quantity that is being returned.

709.name: PosTransType
709.desc: Identifies the type of position transaction

710.name: PosReqID
710.desc: Unique identifier for the position maintenance request as assigned by the submitter

711.name: NoUnderlyings
711.desc: Number of underlying legs that make up the security.

713.name: OrigPosReqRefID
713.desc: Reference to the PosReqID (710) of a previous maintenance request that is being replaced or canceled.

714.desc: Reference to a PosMaintRptID (721) from a previous Position Maintenance Report (AM) that is being replaced or canceled.

715.name: ClearingBusinessDate
715.desc: The "Clearing Business Date" referred to by this maintenance request.

718.name: AdjustmentType
718.desc: Type of adjustment to be applied, used for PCS and PAJ

719.name: ContraryInstructionIndicator
719.desc: Used to indicate when a contrary instruction for exercise or abandonment is being submitted

720.name: PriorSpreadIndicator

721.name: PosMaintRptID
721.desc: Unique identifier for this Position Report (AP)

724.name: PosReqType
724.desc: Used to specify the type of Position Maintenance Request (AL) being made.

725.name: ResponseTransportType
725.desc: Identifies how the response to the request should be transmitted.

726.name: ResponseDestination
726.desc: URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) for details) or other pre-arranged value. Used in conjunction with ResponseTransportType (725) value of Out-of-Band to identify the out-of-band destination.

727.desc: Total number of Position Reports being returned.

735.name: NoQuoteQualifiers
735.desc: Number of repeating groups of QuoteQualifiers (695).

736.name: AllocSettlCurrency
736.desc: Currency code of settlement denomination for a specific AllocAccount (79) .

737.desc: Total amount due expressed in settlement currency (includes the effect of the forex transaction) for a specific AllocAccount (79) .

738.desc: Amount of interest (i.e. lump-sum) at maturity.

740.name: LegPool
740.desc: For Fixed Income, identifies MBS / ABS pool for a specific leg of a multi-leg instrument.

741.name: AllocInterestAtMaturity
741.desc: Amount of interest (i.e. lump-sum) at maturity at the account-level.

742.name: AllocAccruedInterestAmt
742.desc: Amount of Accrued Interest for convertible bonds and fixed income at the allocation-level.

744.name: AssignmentMethod
744.desc: Method by which short positions are assigned to an exercise notice during exercise and assignment processing

748.desc: Total number of trade reports returned.

751.name: TradeReportRejectReason

752.name: SideMultiLegReportingType
752.desc: Used to indicate if the side being reported on Trade Capture Report (AE) represents a leg of a multileg instrument or a single security.

754.name: AutoAcceptIndicator
754.desc: Identifies whether or not an allocation has been automatically accepted on behalf of the Carry Firm by the Clearing House.

755.name: AllocReportID
755.desc: Unique identifier for Allocation Report message.

756.name: NoNested2PartyIDs
756.desc: Number of Nested2PartyID (757) , Nested2PartyIDSource (758) , and Nested2PartyRole (759) entries

757.desc: PartyID value within a "second instance" Nested repeating group.

758.name: Nested2PartyIDSource
758.desc: PartyIDSource value within a "second instance" Nested repeating group.

759.desc: PartyRole value within a "second instance" Nested repeating group.

760.desc: PartySubID value within a "second instance" Nested repeating group.

762.desc: Sub-type qualification/identification of the SecurityType (167) (e.g. for SecurityType (167) ="REPO").

765.desc: The maximum percentage that execution of one side of a program trade can exceed execution of the other.

772.desc: Reference identifier to be used with ConfirmTransType (666) = Replace or Cancel

773.name: ConfirmType
773.desc: Identifies the type of Confirmation (AK) message being sent.

775.desc: Method for booking out this order. Used when notifying a broker that an order to be settled by that broker is to be booked out as an OTC derivative (e.g. CFD or similar).

776.desc: Identified reason for rejecting an individual AllocAccount (79) detail.

777.name: SettlInstMsgID
777.desc: Unique identifier for Settlement Instructions (T) message.

778.desc: Number of settlement instructions within repeating group.

779.desc: Timestamp of last update to data item (or creation if no updates made since creation).

780.desc: Used to indicate whether settlement instructions are provided on an allocation instruction (J) message, and if not, how they are to be derived.

781.desc: Number of SettlPartyID (782) , SettlPartyIDSource (783) , and SettlPartyRole (784) entries.

782.name: SettlPartyID
782.desc: PartyID value within a settlement parties component. Nested repeating group.

783.name: SettlPartyIDSource
783.desc: PartyIDSource value within a settlement parties component.

784.name: SettlPartyRole
784.desc: PartyRole value within a settlement parties component.

785.name: SettlPartySubID
785.desc: PartySubID value within a settlement parties component.

787.desc: Used to indicate whether a delivery instruction is used for securities or cash settlement.

789.name: NextExpectedMsgSeqNum
789.desc: Next expected MsgSeqNum (34) value to be received.

790.name: OrdStatusReqID
790.desc: Can be used to uniquely identify a specific Order Status Request (H) message.

792.desc: Identifies reason for rejection (of a Settlement Instruction Request (AV) message).

Unlike the AllocID (70) , this can be shared across a number of allocation instruction (J) or allocation report (AS) messages, thereby making it possible to pass an identifier for an original allocation (J) message on multiple messages (e.g. from one party to a second to a third, across cancel and replace messages etc.).

794.name: AllocReportType
794.desc: Describes the specific type or purpose of an Allocation Report (AS) message.

795.name: AllocReportRefID
795.desc: Reference identifier to be used with AllocTransType (71) = Replace or Cancel.

796.name: AllocCancReplaceReason
796.desc: Reason for cancelling or replacing an Allocation Instruction (J) or Allocation Report (AS) message.

797.name: CopyMsgIndicator
797.desc: Indicates whether or not this message is a drop copy of another message.

798.name: AllocAccountType
798.desc: Type of account associated with a confirmation or other trade-level message

799.name: OrderAvgPx
799.desc: Average price for a specific order.

800.name: OrderBookingQty
800.desc: Quantity of the order that is being booked out as part of an Allocation Instruction (J) or Allocation Report (AS) message.

801.name: NoSettlPartySubIDs
801.desc: Number of SettlPartySubID (785) and SettlPartySubIDType (786) entries

802.name: NoPartySubIDs
802.desc: Number of PartySubID (523) and PartySubIDType (803) entries

804.name: NoNestedPartySubIDs
804.desc: Number of NestedPartySubID (545) and NestedPartySubIDType (805) entries.

806.name: NoNested2PartySubIDs
806.desc: Number of Nested2PartySubID (760) and Nested2PartySubIDType (807) entries. Second instance of NestedParties .

807.name: Nested2PartySubIDType
807.desc: Type of Nested2PartySubID (760) value. Second instance of NestedParties .

808.desc: Response to allocation to be communicated to a counterparty through an intermediary, i.e. clearing house. Used in conjunction with AllocType (626) = "Request to Intermediary" and AllocReportType (794) = "Request to Intermediary"

810.name: UnderlyingPx
810.desc: Underlying price associate with a derivative instrument.

812.name: ApplQueueMax
812.desc: Used to specify the maximum number of application messages that can be queued bedore a corrective action needs to take place to resolve the queuing issue.

813.desc: Current number of application messages that were queued at the time that the message was created by the counterparty.

814.desc: Resolution taken when ApplQueueDepth (813) exceeds ApplQueueMax (812) or system specified maximum queue size.

815.name: ApplQueueAction
815.desc: Action to take to resolve an application message queue (backlog).

816.name: NoAltMDSource

817.name: AltMDSourceID
817.desc: Session layer source for market data.

818.name: SecondaryTradeReportID

820.name: TradeLinkID
820.desc: Used to link a group of trades together. Useful for linking a group of trades together for average price calculations.

821.name: OrderInputDevice
821.desc: Specific device number, terminal number or station where order was entered

822.name: UnderlyingTradingSessionID
822.desc: Trading Session in which the underlying instrument trades

823.name: UnderlyingTradingSessionSubID
823.desc: Trading Session sub identifier in which the underlying instrument trades

824.name: TradeLegRefID
824.desc: Reference to the leg of a multileg instrument to which this trade refers

825.name: ExchangeRule

826.name: TradeAllocIndicator
826.desc: Identifies how the trade is to be allocated

827.name: ExpirationCycle

829.name: TrdSubType
829.desc: Further qualification to the trade type

832.name: TotNumAssignmentReports
832.desc: Total Number of Assignment Reports being returned to a firm.

833.name: AsgnRptID
833.desc: Unique identifier for the Assignment Report (AW) .

834.name: ThresholdAmount
834.desc: Amount that a position has to be in the money before it is exercised.

835.name: PegMoveType
835.desc: Describes whether peg is static or floats.

838.desc: If the calculated peg price is not a valid tick price, specifies whether to round the price to be more or less aggressive.

839.desc: The price the order is currently pegged at.

841.name: DiscretionMoveType

844.name: DiscretionRoundDirection
844.desc: If the calculated discretionary price is not a valid tick price, specifies whether to round the price to be more or less aggressive.

845.name: DiscretionPrice
845.desc: The current discretionary price of the order.

847.name: TargetStrategy

848.name: TargetStrategyParameters
848.desc: Deprecated in FIX.5.0 Field to allow further specification of the TargetStrategy (847) - usage to be agreed between counterparties.

852.desc: Indicates if a trade should be reported via a market reporting service.

854.name: QtyType

855.name: SecondaryTrdType
855.desc: Additional TrdType (828) assigned to a trade by trade match system.

857.desc: Indicates how the orders being booked and allocated by an Allocation Instruction (J) or Allocation Report (AS) message are identified, i.e. by explicit definition in the NoOrders (73) group or not.

859.name: ConfirmReqID
859.desc: Unique identifier for a Confirmation Request message.

860.desc: Used to express average price as percent of par (used where AvgPx (6) field is expressed in some other way).

863.name: OrderCapacityQty
863.desc: Quantity executed under a specific OrderCapacity (e.g. quantity executed as agent, quantity executed as principal).

865.name: EventType
865.desc: Code to represent the type of event

867.name: EventPx

869.name: PctAtRisk

872.name: InstrAttribValue
872.desc: Attribute value appropriate to the InstrAttribType (871) field.

875.name: CPProgram
875.desc: The program under which a commercial paper is issued

876.name: CPRegType
876.desc: The registration type of a commercial paper issuance.

886.name: UnderlyingEndValue
