899.name: MarginExcess
899.desc: Excess margin amount (deficit if value is negative)

907.name: CollAsgnRefID
907.desc: Collateral Assignment (AY) Identifier to which a transaction refers.

911.name: TotNumReports
911.desc: Total number or reports returned in response to a request.

912.name: LastRptRequested
912.desc: Indicates whether this message is that last report message in response to a request, such as Order Mass Status Request (AF) .

913.name: AgreementDesc
913.desc: The full name of the base standard agreement, annexes and amendments in place between the principals applicable to a financing transaction.

914.name: AgreementID
914.desc: A common reference to the applicable standing agreement between the counterparties to a financing transaction.

915.name: AgreementDate
915.desc: A reference to the date the underlying agreement specified by AgreementID (914) and AgreementDesc (913) was executed.

916.name: StartDate
916.desc: Start date of a financing deal, i.e. the date the buyer pays the seller cash and takes control of the collateral.

917.name: EndDate
917.desc: End date of a financing deal, i.e. the date the seller reimburses the buyer and takes back control of the collateral.

918.name: AgreementCurrency
918.desc: Contractual currency forming the basis of a financing agreement and associated transactions. Usually, but not always, the same as the trade currency.

920.name: EndAccruedInterestAmt
920.desc: Accrued Interest Amount applicable to a financing transaction on the End Date.

921.name: StartCash
921.desc: Starting dirty cash consideration of a financing deal, i.e. paid to the seller on the Start Date.

922.name: EndCash
922.desc: Ending dirty cash consideration of a financing deal. i.e. reimbursed to the buyer on the End Date.

923.name: UserRequestID
923.desc: Unique identifier for a User Request (BE) .

924.name: UserRequestType
924.desc: Indicates the action required by a User Request (BE) Message.

926.name: UserStatus
926.desc: Indicates the status of a user

927.name: UserStatusText
927.desc: A text description associated with a user status.

928.name: StatusValue
928.desc: Indicates the status of a network connection

929.name: StatusText
929.desc: A text description associated with a network status.

930.name: RefCompID
930.desc: Assigned value used to identify a firm.

931.name: RefSubID
931.desc: Assigned value used to identify specific elements within a firm.

932.name: NetworkResponseID
932.desc: Unique identifier for a network response.

933.name: NetworkRequestID
933.desc: Unique identifier for a network resquest.

934.name: LastNetworkResponseID
934.desc: Identifier of the previous Network (Counterparty System) Status Response (BD) message sent to a counterparty, used to allow incremental updates.

935.name: NetworkRequestType
935.desc: Indicates the type and level of details required for a Network (Counterparty System) Status Request (BC) Message

936.name: NoCompIDs
936.desc: Number of CompID entries in a repeating group.

937.name: NetworkStatusResponseType
937.desc: Indicates the type of Network (Counterparty System) Status Response (BD) Message.

938.name: NoCollInquiryQualifier
938.desc: Number of CollInquiryQualifier entries in a repeating group.

940.name: AffirmStatus
940.desc: Identifies the status of the Confirmation Ack (AU) .

941.name: UnderlyingStrikeCurrency
941.desc: Currency in which the strike price of an underlying instrument is denominated

942.name: LegStrikeCurrency
942.desc: Currency in which the strike price of a instrument leg of a multileg instrument is denominated.

943.name: TimeBracket
943.desc: A code that represents a time interval in which a fill or trade occurred.

944.name: CollAction
944.desc: Action proposed for an Underlying Instrument instance.

946.name: CollInquiryResult
946.desc: Result returned in response to Collateral Inquiry (BB) .

947.name: StrikeCurrency
947.desc: Currency in which the StrikePrice (202) is denominated.

948.name: NoNested3PartyIDs
948.desc: Number of Nested3PartyID (949) , Nested3PartyIDSource (950) , and Nested3PartyRole (951) entries

949.name: Nested3PartyID
949.desc: PartyID value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group.

950.name: Nested3PartyIDSource
950.desc: PartyIDSource value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group.

951.name: Nested3PartyRole
951.desc: PartyRole value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group.

953.name: Nested3PartySubID
953.desc: PartySubID value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group.

954.name: Nested3PartySubIDType
954.desc: PartySubIDType value within a "third instance" Nested repeating group.

955.name: LegContractSettlMonth
955.desc: Specifies when the contract (i.e. MBS/TBA) will settle.

956.name: LegInterestAccrualDate
956.desc: The start date used for calculating accrued interest on debt instruments which are being sold between interest payment dates. Often but not always the same as the IssueDate (225) and the DatedDate (873)

961.name: HostCrossID
961.desc: Host assigned entity ID that can be used to reference all components of a cross; sides + strategy + legs. Used as the primary key with which to refer to the Cross Order for cancellation and replace. The HostCrossID will also be used to link together components of the Cross Order. For example, each individual Execution Report associated with the order will carry HostCrossID in order to tie back to the original cross order.

962.name: SideTimeInForce
962.desc: Indicates how long the order as specified in the side stays in effect. SideTimeInForce allows a two-sided cross order to specify order behavior separately for each side. Absence of this field indicates that TimeInForce should be referenced. SideTimeInForce will override TimeInForce if both are provided.

963.name: MDReportID
963.desc: Unique identifier for the Market Data Report.

964.name: SecurityReportID
964.desc: Security Report ID. Unique identifier for the Security Report.

965.name: SecurityStatus
965.desc: Used for derivatives. Denotes the current state of the Instrument.

966.name: SettleOnOpenFlag
966.desc: Indicator to determine if instrument is settle on open.

967.name: StrikeMultiplier
967.desc: Used for derivatives. Multiplier applied to the strike price for the purpose of calculating the settlement value.

968.name: StrikeValue
968.desc: Used for derivatives. The number of shares/units for the financial instrument involved in the option trade.

969.name: MinPriceIncrement
969.desc: Minimum price increase for a given exchange-traded Instrument

970.name: PositionLimit
970.desc: Position Limit for a given exchange-traded product.

971.name: NTPositionLimit
971.desc: Position Limit in the near-term contract for a given exchange-traded product.

972.name: UnderlyingAllocationPercent
972.desc: Percent of the Strike Price that this underlying represents.

973.name: UnderlyingCashAmount
973.desc: Cash amount associated with the underlying component.

974.name: UnderlyingCashType
974.desc: Specific to the <UnderlyingInstrument> Used for derivatives that deliver into cash underlying.

975.name: UnderlyingSettlementType
975.desc: Indicates order settlement period for the underlying instrument.

976.name: QuantityDate
976.desc: Date associated to the quantity that is being reported for the position.

977.name: ContIntRptID
977.desc: Unique identifier for the Contrary Intention report.

978.name: LateIndicator
978.desc: Indicates if the contrary intention was received after the exchange imposed cutoff time.

983.name: ExpQty
983.desc: Expiration Quantity associated with the Expiration Type.

984.name: NoUnderlyingAmounts
984.desc: Total number of occurrences of Amount to pay in order to receive the underlying instrument.

985.name: UnderlyingPayAmount
985.desc: Amount to pay in order to receive the underlying instrument.

986.name: UnderlyingCollectAmount
986.desc: Amount to collect in order to deliver the underlying instrument.

987.name: UnderlyingSettlementDate
987.desc: Date the underlying instrument will settle. Used for derivatives that deliver into more than one underlying instrument. Settlement dates can vary across underlying instruments.

988.name: UnderlyingSettlementStatus
988.desc: Settlement status of the underlying instrument. Used for derivatives that deliver into more than one underlying instrument. Settlement can be delayed for an underlying instrument.

989.name: SecondaryIndividualAllocID
989.desc: Will allow the intermediary to specify an allocation ID generated by their system.

990.name: LegReportID
990.desc: Additional attribute to store the Trade ID of the Leg.

991.name: RndPx
991.desc: Specifies average price rounded to quoted precision.

992.name: IndividualAllocType
992.desc: Identifies whether the allocation is to be sub-allocated or allocated to a third party.

993.name: AllocCustomerCapacity
993.desc: Capacity of customer in the allocation block.

994.name: TierCode
994.desc: The Tier the trade was matched by the clearing system.

996.name: UnitofMeasure
996.desc: Physical unit of measure for Derivative products.

997.name: TimeUnit
997.desc: Unit of time associated with the contract.

1002.name: AllocMethod
1002.desc: Specifies the method under which a trade quantity was allocated.

1003.name: TradeID
1003.desc: The unique ID assigned to the trade entity once it is received or matched by the exchange or central counterparty.

1005.name: SideTradeReportID
1005.desc: Used on a multi-sided trade to designate the ReportID.

1006.name: SideFillStationCd
1006.desc: Used on a multi-sided trade to convey order routing information.

1007.name: SideReasonCd
1007.desc: Used on a multi-sided trade to convey reason for execution.

1008.name: SideTrdSubTyp
1008.desc: Used on a multi-sided trade to specify the type of trade for a given side.

1009.name: SideQty
1009.desc: Used to indicate the quantity on one of a multi-sided Trade Capture Report.

1011.name: MessageEventSource
1011.desc: Used to identify the event or source which gave rise to a message.

1012.name: SideTrdRegTimestamp
1012.desc: Will be used in a multi-sided message.

1015.name: AsOfIndicator
1015.desc: Used to indicate that a floor-trade was originally submitted "as of" a specific trade date which is earlier than its clearing date.

1016.name: NoSideTrdRegTS
1016.desc: Indicates number of SideTimestamps contained in group.

1017.name: LegOptionRatio
1017.desc: Expresses the risk of an option leg

1018.name: NoInstrumentParties
1018.desc: Identifies the number of parties identified with an instrument.

1019.name: InstrumentPartyID
1019.desc: PartyID value within an instrument party repeating group. Same values as PartyID (448) .

1020.name: TradeVolume
1020.desc: Used to report volume with a trade.

1021.name: MDBookType
1021.desc: Describes the type of book for which the feed is intended. Used when multiple feeds are provided over the same connection.

1022.name: MDFeedType
1022.desc: Describes a class of service for a given data feed, ie Regular and Market Maker, Bandwidth Intensive or Bandwidth Conservative.

1023.name: MDPriceLevel
1023.desc: Integer to convey the level of a bid or offer at a given price level. This is in contrast to MDEntryPositionNo which is used to convey the position of an order within a Price level.

1024.name: MDOriginType
1024.desc: Used to describe the origin of an entry in the book.

1025.name: FirstPx
1025.desc: Indicates the first trade price of the day/session.

1026.name: MDEntrySpotRate
1026.desc: The spot rate for an FX entry.

1027.name: MDEntryForwardPoints
1027.desc: Used for an F/X entry. The forward points to be added to or subtracted from the spot rate to get the "all-in" rate in MDEntryPx. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

1028.name: ManualOrderIndicator
1028.desc: Indicates if the order was initially received manually (as opposed to electronically)

1029.name: CustDirectedOrder
1029.desc: Indicates if the customer directed this order to a specific execution venue (Y) or not (N). A default of N customer didnt direct this order should beused in the case where the information is both missing and essential.

1030.name: ReceivedDeptID
1030.desc: Identifies the Broker / Dealer Department that first took the order.

1031.name: CustOrderHandlingInst
1031.desc: Codes that apply special information that the Broker / Dealer needs to report, as specified by the customer.

1032.name: OrderHandlingInstSource
1032.desc: Identifies the class or source of the OrderHandlingInst values. Scope of this will apply to both CustOrderHandlingInst and DeskOrderHandlingInst fields.

1035.name: DeskOrderHandlingInst
1035.desc: Codes that apply special information that the Broker / Dealer needs to report

1036.name: ExecAckStatus
1036.desc: The status of this execution acknowledgement message.

1037.name: UnderlyingDeliveryAmount
1037.desc: Indicates the underlying position amount to be delivered

1038.name: UnderlyingCapValue
1038.desc: Maximum notional value for a capped financial instrument

1040.name: SecondaryTradeID
1040.desc: Used to carry an internal trade entity ID which may or may not be reported to the firm

1041.name: FirmTradeID
1041.desc: The ID assigned to a trade by the Firm to track a trade within the Firm system. This ID can be assigned either before or after submission to the exchange or central counterpary

1042.name: SecondaryFirmTradeID
1042.desc: Used to carry an internal firm assigned ID which may or may not be reported to the exchange or central counterpary.

1043.name: CollApplType
1043.desc: Conveys how the collateral should be/has been applied.

1044.name: UnderlyingAdjustedQuantity
1044.desc: Unit amount of the underlying security (shares) adjusted for pending corporate action not yet allocated.

1045.name: UnderlyingFXRate
1045.desc: Foreign exchange rate used to compute UnderlyingCurrentValue (885) (or market value) from UnderlyingCurrency (318) to Currency (15) .

1046.name: UnderlyingFXRateCalc
1046.desc: Specifies whether the UnderlyingFXRate (1045) should be multiplied or divided.

1047.name: AllocPositionEffect
1047.desc: Indicates whether the resulting position after a trade should be an opening position or closing position. Used for omnibus accounting - where accounts are held on a gross basis instead of being netted together.

1048.name: DealingCapacity
1048.desc: Identifies role of dealer; Agent, Principal, RisklessPrincipal

1049.name: InstrmtAssignmentMethod
1049.desc: Method under which assignment was conducted

1050.name: InstrumentPartyIDSource
1050.desc: PartyIDSource value within an instrument partyrepeating group.

1051.name: InstrumentPartyRole
1051.desc: PartyRole value within an instrument partyepeating group.

1052.name: NoInstrumentPartySubIDs
1052.desc: Number of InstrumentPartySubID (1053) and InstrumentPartySubIDType (1054) entries

1053.name: InstrumentPartySubID
1053.desc: PartySubID value within an instrument party repeating group.

1055.name: PositionCurrency
1055.desc: The Currency in which the position Amount is denominated.

1056.name: CalculatedCcyLastQty
1056.desc: Used for the calculated quantity of the other side of the currency trade. Can be derived from LastQty and LastPx.

1057.name: AggressorIndicator
1057.desc: Used to identify whether the order initiator is an aggressor or not in the trade.

1058.name: NoUndlyInstrumentParties
1058.desc: Identifies the number of parties identified with an underlying instrument.

1059.name: UndlyInstrumentPartyID
1059.desc: PartyID value within an underlying instrument party repeating group.

1060.name: UndlyInstrumentPartyIDSource
1060.desc: PartyIDSource value within an underlying instrument partyrepeating group.

1061.name: UndlyInstrumentPartyRole
1061.desc: PartyRole value within an underlying instrument partyepeating group.

1062.name: NoUndlyInstrumentPartySubIDs
1062.desc: Number of Underlying InstrumentPartySubID (1053) and InstrumentPartySubIDType (1054) entries

1063.name: UndlyInstrumentPartySubID
1063.desc: PartySubID value within an underlying instrument party repeating group.

1065.name: BidSwapPoints
1065.desc: The bid FX Swap points for an FX Swap. It is the "far bid forward points - near offer forward point". Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

1066.name: OfferSwapPoints
1066.desc: The offer FX Swap points for an FX Swap. It is the "far offer forward points - near bid forward points". Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

1067.name: LegBidForwardPoints
1067.desc: The bid FX forward points for the leg of an FX Swap. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

1068.name: LegOfferForwardPoints
1068.desc: The offer FX forward points for the leg of an FX Swap. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

1069.name: SwapPoints
1069.desc: For FX Swap, this is used to express the differential between the far leg's bid/offer and the near leg's bid/offer. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

1071.name: LastSwapPoints
1071.desc: For FX Swap, this is used to express the last market event for the differential between the far leg's bid/offer and the near leg's bid/offer in a fill or partial fill. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

1072.name: SideGrossTradeAmt
1072.desc: The gross trade amount for this side of the trade. See also GrossTradeAmt (381) , for additional definition.

1073.name: LegLastForwardPoints
1073.desc: The forward points for this leg's fill event. Value can be negative. Expressed in decimal form. For example, 61.99 points is expressed and sent as 0.006199

1074.name: LegCalculatedCcyLastQty
1074.desc: Used for the calculated quantity of the other side of the currency for this leg. Can be derived from LegQty and LegLastPx.

1075.name: LegGrossTradeAmt
1075.desc: The gross trade amount of the leg. For FX Futures this is used to express the notional value of a fill when LegLastQty and other quantity fields are express in terms of contract size.

1079.name: MaturityTime
1079.desc: Time of security's maturity expressed in local time with offset to UTC specified.

1080.name: RefOrderID
1080.desc: The ID reference to the order being hit or taken.

1081.name: RefOrderIDSource
1081.desc: Used to specify what identifier, provided in order depth market data, to use when hitting (taking) a specific order.

1082.name: SecondaryDisplayQty
1082.desc: Used for reserve orders when DisplayQty applies to the primary execution market (e.g.an ECN) and another quantity is to be shown at other markets (e.g. the exchange). On orders specifies the qty to be displayed, on execution reports the currently displayed quantity.

1084.name: DisplayMethod
1084.desc: Defines what value to use in DisplayQty (1138) . If not specified the default DisplayMethod is "1".

1085.name: DisplayLowQty
1085.desc: Defines the lower quantity limit to a randomized refresh of DisplayQty (1138) .

1086.name: DisplayHighQty
1086.desc: Defines the upper quantity limit to a randomized refresh of DisplayQty (1138) .

1087.name: DisplayMinIncr
1087.desc: Defines the minimum increment to be used when calculating a random refresh of DisplayQty (1138) . A user specifies this when he wants a larger increment than the standard provided by the market (e.g. the round lot size).

1088.name: RefreshQty
1088.desc: Defines the quantity used to refresh DisplayQty (1138) .

1089.name: MatchIncrement
1089.desc: Allows orders to specify a minimum quantity that applies to every execution (one execution could be for multiple counter-orders). The order may still fill against smaller orders, but the cumulative quantity of the execution must be in multiples of the MatchIncrement.

1090.name: MaxPriceLevels
1090.desc: Allows an order to specify a maximum number of price levels to trade through. Only valid for aggressive orders and during continuous (autoexecution) trading sessions. Property lost when order is put on book. A partially filled order is assigned last trade price as limit price. Non-filled order behaves as ordinary Market or Limit.

1091.name: PreTradeAnonymity
1091.desc: Allows trader to explicitly request anonymity or disclosure in pre-trade market data feeds. Anonymity is relevant in markets where counterparties are regularly disclosed in order depth feeds. Disclosure is relevant when counterparties are not normally visible.

1092.name: PriceProtectionScope
1092.desc: Defines the type of price protection the customer requires on their order.

1093.name: LotType
1093.desc: Defines the lot type assigned to the order.

1095.name: PeggedRefPrice
1095.desc: The value of the reference price that the order is pegged to. PeggedRefPrice + PegOffsetValue (211) = PeggedPrice (839) unless the limit price ( Price (44) ) is breached. The values may not be exact due to rounding.

1096.name: PegSecurityIDSource
1096.desc: Defines the identity of the security off whose prices the order will peg.

1097.name: PegSecurityID
1097.desc: Defines the identity of the security off whose prices the order will peg.

1098.name: PegSymbol
1098.desc: Defines the common, 'human understood' representation of the security off whose prices the order will Peg.

1099.name: PegSecurityDesc
1099.desc: Security description of the security off whose prices the order will Peg.

1100.name: TriggerType
1100.desc: Defines when the trigger will hit, i.e. the action specified by the trigger instructions will come into effect.

1101.name: TriggerAction
1101.desc: Defines the type of action to take when the trigger hits.

1102.name: TriggerPrice
1102.desc: The price at which the trigger should hit.

1103.name: TriggerSymbol
1103.desc: Defines the common, 'human understood' representation of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

1104.name: TriggerSecurityID
1104.desc: Defines the identity of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

1105.name: TriggerSecurityIDSource
1105.desc: Defines the identity of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

1106.name: TriggerSecurityDesc
1106.desc: Defines the security description of the security whose prices will be tracked by the trigger logic.

1107.name: TriggerPriceType
1107.desc: The type of price that the trigger is compared to.

1108.name: TriggerPriceTypeScope
1108.desc: Defines the type of price protection the customer requires on their order.

1109.name: TriggerPriceDirection
1109.desc: The side from which the trigger price is reached.

1110.name: TriggerNewPrice
1110.desc: The Price that the order should have after the trigger has hit. Could be applicable for any trigger type, but must be specified for Trigger Type 1.

1111.name: TriggerOrderType
1111.desc: The OrdType the order should have after the trigger has hit. Required to express orders that change from Limit to Market. Other values from OrdType (40) may be used if appropriate and bilaterally agreed upon.

1112.name: TriggerNewQty
1112.desc: The Quantity the order should have after the trigger has hit.

1113.name: TriggerTradingSessionID
1113.desc: Defines the trading session at which the order will be activated.

1114.name: TriggerTradingSessionSubID
1114.desc: Defines the subordinate trading session at which the order will be activated.

1115.name: OrderCategory
1115.desc: Defines the type of interest behind a trade (fill or partial fill).

1116.name: NoRootPartyIDs
1116.desc: Number of RootPartyID (1117) , RootPartyIDSource (1118) , and RootPartyRole (1119) entries.

1117.name: RootPartyID
1117.desc: PartyID value within a root parties component. Same values as PartyID (448) .

1118.name: RootPartyIDSource
1118.desc: PartyIDSource value within a root parties component.

1119.name: RootPartyRole
1119.desc: PartyRole value within a root parties component.

1120.name: NoRootPartySubIDs
1120.desc: Number of RootPartySubID (1121) and RootPartySubIDType (1122) entries

1121.name: RootPartySubID
1121.desc: PartySubID value within a root parties component. Same values as PartySubID (523)

1122.name: RootPartySubIDType
1122.desc: Type of RootPartySubID (1121) value. Same values as PartySubIDType (803)

1123.name: TradeHandlingInstr
1123.desc: Specified how the Trade Capture Report should be handled by the Respondent.

1124.name: OrigTradeHandlingInstr
1124.desc: Optionally used with TradeHandlingInstr = 0 to relay the trade handling instruction used when reporting the trade to the marketplace. Same values as TradeHandlingInstr (1123)

1125.name: OrigTradeDate
1125.desc: Used to preserve original trade date when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

1126.name: OrigTradeID
1126.desc: Used to preserve original trade id when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

1127.name: OrigSecondaryTradeID
1127.desc: Used to preserve original secondary trade id when original trade is being referenced in a subsequent trade transaction such as a transfer

1128.name: ApplVerID
1128.desc: Specifies the service pack release being applied at message level. Enumerated field with values assigned at time of service pack release

1129.name: CstmApplVerID
1129.desc: Specifies a custom extension to a message being applied at the message level. Enumerated field

1130.name: RefApplVerID
1130.desc: Specifies the service pack release being applied to a message at the session level. Enumerated field with values assigned at time of service pack release. Uses same values as ApplVerID

1131.name: RefCstmApplVerID
1131.desc: Specifies a custom extension to a message being applied at the session level.

1132.name: TZTransactTime
1132.desc: Transact time in the local date-time stamp with a TZ offset to UTC identified

1134.name: ReportedPxDiff
1134.desc: Shows that the reported price that is different from the market price.

1135.name: RptSys
1135.desc: Indicates the system or medium on which the report has been published.

1136.name: AllocClearingFeeIndicator
1136.desc: ClearingFeeIndicator (635) for Allocation, see ClearingFeeIndicator (635) for permitted values.

1137.name: DefaultApplVerID
1137.desc: Specifies the service pack release being applied, by default, to message at the session level. Enumerated field with values assigned at time of service pack release. Uses same values as ApplVerID

1138.name: DisplayQty
1138.desc: The quantity to be displayed . Required for reserve orders. On orders specifies the qty to be displayed, on execution reports the currently displayed quantity.

1139.name: ExchangeSpecialInstructions
1139.desc: Free format test string related to exchange.
